HEADWORD: Reluct
<hw>Re*luct"</hw> <pr>(r?-l?kt")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>reluctari</ets>, p. p. <ets>reluctatus</ets>, to struggle; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>luctari</ets> to struggle, fr.
<ets>lucia</ets> a wresting.]</ety> <def>To strive or struggle against
anything; to make resistance; to draw back; to feel or show repugnance
or reluctance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Apt to <qex>reluct</qex> at the excesses of it [passion].</q>
<rj><qau>Walton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reluctancy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Reluctance</ent>⟦br⟧
